# Selection Sort - Quick Revision Notes

## 1. What is Selection Sort?

Selection Sort is a simple sorting algorithm that repeatedly:

1. Finds the smallest element from the unsorted part of the array.
2. Places it at its correct position.
3. Moves the boundary of the sorted portion one step forward.

### Key Idea

> "Select the minimum element and place it in the correct position."

# 3. Algorithm

For each position:

1. Assume current index is minimum.
2. Search remaining array for smaller element.
3. Update minimum index if found.
4. Swap minimum element with current position.


# 5. Java Implementation

```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class SelectionSort {

    public static void selectionSort(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

            int minIndex = i;

            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {

                if (arr[j] < arr[minIndex]) {
                    minIndex = j;
                }
            }

            int temp = arr[i];
            arr[i] = arr[minIndex];
            arr[minIndex] = temp;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {64, 25, 12, 22, 11};

        selectionSort(arr);

        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
    }
}
```
